==English==

{{rank|sufficient|conduct|directly|931|James|Greek|island|special}}

===Pronunciation===
*/dʒeɪmz/

===Etymology===
Came into English from the {{F.}} variation [[Gemmes]] of the {{LL.}} '''[[Iacomus]]''', dialect variant of '''[[Iacobus]]''', from New Testament {{Gr.}} '''[[Ἰάκωβος]]''' (Iacōbos), from {{Hebr.}} '''[[יעקב]]''' (Yaʻaqov). Cognates include '''[[Jacob]]'''

===Proper noun===
'''James'''
# An [[English]] male [[given name]] meaning "held by the heel, protected, supplanted."
# An English [[surname]] derived from the given name

  3. A slang term for a gay pole dancer that originated in london, A JAMES

